{{infobox website | name = {{Wiki favicon}} Extremaduran Wikipedia | logo = File:Wikipedia-logo-v2-ext.svg | screenshot = | collapsible = | caption = | url = {{URL|ext.wikipedia.org}} | commercial = No | location = | type = [[Internet encyclopedia project]] | language = [[Extremaduran language|Extremaduran]] | registration = Optional | owner = [[Wikimedia Foundation]] | launch date = {{start date and age|2007|1|27}} | author = }} The '''Extremaduran Wikipedia''' ({{lang-ext|Wikipedia en estremeñu|{{#property:P1448}}}}) or '''Güiquipeya'''<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.publico.es/ciencias/67681/llega-la-guiquipeya |title=Llega la Güiquipeya| editor=[[Público (Spain)|Público.es]]| language=es| accessdate=3 February 2011|archivedate=19 April 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110419032757/http://www.publico.es:80/ciencias/67681/llega-la-guiquipeya|date=7 April 2008}}</ref> is the [[Extremaduran language|Extremaduran-language]] edition of [[Wikipedia]], a free, online [[encyclopedia]].<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.elpais.com/articulo/Pantallas/extremeno/tiene/edicion/Wikipedia/elpepirtv/20080409elpepirtv_2/Tes| title=El extremeño ya tiene su edición en Wikipedia|editor=[[El País]].com| language=es| accessdate=3 February 2011|date=9 April 2008| place=Madrid}}</ref> It has {{NUMBEROF|ARTICLES|ext|N}} articles. Started on 27 January 2007, although it was not until 28 May 2008 when it obtained its new definitive URL. With more than 1300 entries, it is ranked 205th in the Wikipedia list according to the number of articles.
==Controversy== Different media have criticized the Extremaduran version of Wikipedia. It is questioned that the Extremaduran is not really a language, it is a dialect of [[Asturian language|Asturian]] and [[Spanish language|Castilian]],<ref name="PEx">{{Cite web| url=http://www.elperiodicoextremadura.com/noticias/noticia.asp?pkid=367349&page=9| title=Los 200.000 hablantes del extremeño| work=El Periódico de Extremadura| language=es| accessdate=3 February 2011| date=12 April 2008|archivedate=9 December 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171209113825/http://www.elperiodicoextremadura.com/noticias/extremadura/200-000-hablantes-extremeno_367349.html}}</ref> and that it does not have a defined spelling rule.<ref name="PEx"/> The fact that the page only has three main contributors, the same who initiated the project has also been the subject of controversy.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.hoy.es/20080413/sociedad/verdadera-historia-guiquipeya-20080413.html| title=La verdadera historia de la Güiquipeya| author=Aracely R. Robustillo| work=[[Hoy (Extremadura)|Hoy]].es|language=es| accessdate=3 February 2011}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elperiodicoextremadura.com/noticias/noticia.asp?pkid=366939| work=El Periódico de Extremadura| date=10 April 2008| title=Los padres de la polémica Güiquipeya|language=es| author=Isabel Ramos| accessdate=3 February 2011|archivedate=22 March 2016|deadurl= no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322043543/http://www.elperiodicoextremadura.com/noticias/extremadura/padres-polemica-guiquipeya_366939.html}}</ref>
