| pages= 51–82
| doi= 10.2307/3105760
| jstor= 3105760
}}</ref>
}}
{{term|mignonette}}
{{defn|1=''Same as'' [[#weld|weld]].}}
{{term|mordant}}
{{defn|1=A [[mordant]] is a [[chemical]] used in combination with dye to "fix" the color in the textile [[fibre|fibers]]. By using different mordants, dyers can often obtain a variety of colors and shades from the same dye.<ref>Goodwin (1982), p. 12</ref>}}
{{term|munjeet}}
{{defn|1=''Same as'' [[#Indian madder|Indian madder]].}}
