In [[computer programming]], a '''miswart''' is an inelegant behaviour of a program that turns out to be the best of several possible solutions.<ref>[http://catb.org/jargon/html/M/miswart.html Catb.org: Miswart<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
This word was listed in ''The New Hacker's Dictionary'' (Eric Raymond) but has not achieved any general usage. It is rare.
